1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
https://slama.dev/comeback/

2
00:00:02,750 --> 00:00:03,450
Deserts.

3
00:00:04,950 --> 00:00:11,560
Arid wastelands without a drop of moisture cover over 10% of the Earth's land surface.

4
00:00:12,050 --> 00:00:24,050
The beauty of the desert is alluring at first glance, but if you enter this kingdom of eternal drought, a battle with burning thirst awaits you, and for the weak, even death.

5
00:00:25,250 --> 00:00:25,950
So what?

6
00:00:35,650 --> 00:00:37,250
Every thirst needs a reason.

7
00:01:08,240 --> 00:01:11,880
It can not only survive in this furnace, but even thrive.

8
00:01:12,640 --> 00:01:13,560
Hey, bro?

9
00:01:13,800 --> 00:01:14,260
Yeah?

10
00:01:14,850 --> 00:01:16,920
Have you talked to the building manager lately?

11
00:01:16,920 --> 00:01:17,280
No.

12
00:01:18,320 --> 00:01:18,920
Great.

13
00:01:18,920 --> 00:01:20,150
The Bedouins liken me to a coffee plant.

14
00:01:21,280 --> 00:01:24,380
A gift from God, perhaps for its versatile use.

15
00:01:24,540 --> 00:01:28,280
The Bactrian camel can survive without drinking for up to two months.

16
00:01:29,180 --> 00:01:29,780
Incredible.

17
00:01:30,250 --> 00:01:32,900
Yeah, you didn't even go near her.

18
00:01:32,900 --> 00:01:33,500
What?

19
00:01:34,450 --> 00:01:35,950
No, since you told me not to.

20
00:01:36,080 --> 00:01:36,680
Great.

21
00:01:37,750 --> 00:01:39,750
I'm writing a request for a new water heater.

22
00:01:40,650 --> 00:01:42,950
I hope she's forgotten you're my brother by now.

23
00:01:44,550 --> 00:01:46,750
It excels at spitting.

24
00:01:46,950 --> 00:01:49,960
It can spit over great distances with surprising accuracy.

25
00:01:49,960 --> 00:01:51,060
If only I could spit like that.

26
00:01:52,050 --> 00:01:54,020
I wouldn't have missed the building manager from that window yesterday.

27
00:01:55,450 --> 00:01:58,530
Not only does it spit saliva, but also partially digested stomach contents.

28
00:01:58,530 --> 00:01:59,790
I got her all the way from the mezzanine.

29
00:02:01,350 --> 00:02:03,950
Which camel herders try to train out of them in the desert.

30
00:02:04,470 --> 00:02:05,450
Of course, in vain.

31
00:02:13,510 --> 00:02:14,190
Dad, I'm off.

32
00:02:15,850 --> 00:02:17,730
And please don't forget to turn off the chicken.

33
00:02:17,730 --> 00:02:18,210
Where is it?

34
00:02:18,850 --> 00:02:20,050
When it's done.

35
00:02:20,550 --> 00:02:21,690
And how will I know?

36
00:02:21,690 --> 00:02:23,750
God, you poke it with a fork.

37
00:02:24,460 --> 00:02:24,960
And?

38
00:02:25,960 --> 00:02:26,620
What do you mean "and"?

39
00:02:28,350 --> 00:02:30,550
What happens when I poke it with a fork?

40
00:02:31,050 --> 00:02:32,450
You'll know it's done.

41
00:02:34,120 --> 00:02:34,620
Okay.

42
00:02:40,460 --> 00:02:40,960
What?

43
00:02:41,600 --> 00:02:42,100
Nothing.

44
00:02:43,050 --> 00:02:43,850
You were huffing.

45
00:02:44,150 --> 00:02:45,550
I just sighed.

46
00:02:46,050 --> 00:02:48,080
It's healthy, I enjoy it, and I'm good at it.

47
00:02:48,150 --> 00:02:49,850
But you're practically naked doing it.

48
00:02:49,930 --> 00:02:52,670
In belly dancing you have to show the belly, that's obvious, isn't it?

49
00:02:52,670 --> 00:02:56,430
She's too young to be writhing around half-naked somewhere.

50
00:02:56,430 --> 00:02:58,030
Marcel, you said she was too old for it.

51
00:02:58,900 --> 00:03:00,100
That's not what I said.

52
00:03:00,350 --> 00:03:03,150
You said at her age she should maintain her dignity.

53
00:03:03,650 --> 00:03:04,850
I meant well.

54
00:03:06,850 --> 00:03:11,610
Iva, Iva, I tried, but I just can't keep the diamond in my belly button.

55
00:03:11,850 --> 00:03:13,250
Where did you get a diamond?

56
00:03:13,530 --> 00:03:16,630
Well, I tried first with a chestnut and then a ladybug, nothing held.

57
00:03:18,380 --> 00:03:20,240
The bayaderes have the diamonds glued on.

58
00:03:20,850 --> 00:03:21,640
Really?

59
00:03:22,450 --> 00:03:24,850
She'd never do that to a ladybug.

60
00:03:26,350 --> 00:03:35,240
Ladies, I don't want to come across as some old fuddy-duddy, but there are so many lovely Czech national dances.

61
00:03:35,650 --> 00:03:36,650
Like what?

62
00:03:37,550 --> 00:03:39,050
Like the Czech Beseda.

63
00:03:41,650 --> 00:03:48,350
Ladies and gentlemen, the Beseda begins, ladies and gentlemen, the Beseda is on.

64
00:03:49,950 --> 00:03:50,650
We've got the folk costume.

65
00:03:52,850 --> 00:03:53,640
You watch the chicken.

66
00:03:53,640 --> 00:03:54,380
Great!

67
00:04:10,650 --> 00:04:13,950
You're connected to the water heater in the neighboring building.

68
00:04:13,950 --> 00:04:15,340
Through a condensation pipe.

69
00:04:15,950 --> 00:04:17,360
And Pacovsky?

70
00:04:17,360 --> 00:04:18,000
Thanks.

71
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:19,740
And they won't notice.

72
00:04:19,850 --> 00:04:21,080
At home or here?

73
00:04:21,750 --> 00:04:23,690
Here. They're cops, after all.

74
00:04:23,690 --> 00:04:25,870
They're dumber than Pacovsky.

75
00:04:26,070 --> 00:04:26,790
Alright then.

76
00:04:30,250 --> 00:04:30,890
Tomas.

77
00:04:32,350 --> 00:04:33,350
What could he want?

78
00:04:34,590 --> 00:04:35,230
Yeah.

79
00:04:39,650 --> 00:04:40,950
You poke it with a fork.

80
00:04:41,750 --> 00:04:43,550
So you know if the meat comes off the bone.

81
00:04:44,150 --> 00:04:44,950
Bye then.

82
00:04:46,350 --> 00:04:46,990
Easy.

83
00:05:03,600 --> 00:05:04,680
So, how did it go?

84
00:05:04,900 --> 00:05:05,340
Great.

85
00:05:05,440 --> 00:05:06,520
We're going to dance for charity.

86
00:05:07,550 --> 00:05:08,750
In front of people?

87
00:05:09,240 --> 00:05:09,620
Dad.

88
00:05:10,120 --> 00:05:12,660
But you promised you wouldn't do it in public.

89
00:05:12,800 --> 00:05:15,360
No, I said I wouldn't let any strangers into the studio.

90
00:05:15,540 --> 00:05:15,780
Yeah?

91
00:05:15,820 --> 00:05:16,900
And that's true.

92
00:05:17,080 --> 00:05:19,480
Like, they've thrown Lexa out three times already, camera and all.

93
00:05:20,380 --> 00:05:21,200
Good for them.

94
00:05:21,360 --> 00:05:22,220
What kind of event is it?

95
00:05:22,880 --> 00:05:25,040
A charity evening supporting women from developing countries.

96
00:05:25,040 --> 00:05:28,550
The proceeds will go to the Show Your Face campaign so they don't have to wear burqas.

97
00:05:28,950 --> 00:05:30,050
It'll be at the Hilton.

98
00:05:30,450 --> 00:05:32,650
And maybe even the Qatari ambassador will come.

99
00:05:32,850 --> 00:05:39,750
I've got no problem with showing faces, but the fact that you'll be showing everything else to some Arab, that I just don't like.

100
00:05:39,810 --> 00:05:41,350
Sometimes I wonder if you're the Arab here.

101
00:05:41,570 --> 00:05:41,990
What?

102
00:05:42,690 --> 00:05:43,390
What about the chicken?

103
00:05:44,950 --> 00:05:47,010
It's fine, I let it finish.

104
00:05:47,010 --> 00:05:47,450
What?

105
00:05:48,350 --> 00:05:49,150
Finish.

106
00:05:56,350 --> 00:05:56,950
Thing is, I don't want to leave it in the storage room, Ozzak keeps picking at it.

107
00:05:59,810 --> 00:06:01,570
He probably thinks it's beer money.

108
00:06:02,070 --> 00:06:03,290
Good day, Marcelka.

109
00:06:04,460 --> 00:06:04,900
Hello.

110
00:06:05,750 --> 00:06:09,210
I had ten missed calls from you on my phone, did something happen?

111
00:06:09,210 --> 00:06:10,410
No, everything's fine.

112
00:06:11,050 --> 00:06:13,550
So I can delete the text about how to tell when meat comes off the bone.

113
00:06:15,950 --> 00:06:18,320
Ivuska, did you tell your dad the big news?

114
00:06:18,320 --> 00:06:18,480
Yeah.

115
00:06:18,950 --> 00:06:24,840
And is preparing a performance for an important charity event in front of high society dignified enough?

116
00:06:25,050 --> 00:06:26,750
Well, we wouldn't be dancing in burqas.

117
00:06:27,950 --> 00:06:31,150
Now, Iva, don't make me out to be some fuddy-duddy.

118
00:06:32,350 --> 00:06:33,550
Well, I'm off.

119
00:06:33,640 --> 00:06:35,320
I can't wait to take a shower.

120
00:06:35,660 --> 00:06:36,560
Me too.

121
00:06:38,060 --> 00:06:40,120
Hold on, today it's my turn.

122
00:06:40,120 --> 00:06:45,050
But I've been sweating for an hour and you've been sitting by the oven watching your chicken.

123
00:06:59,650 --> 00:07:01,150
Ugh, risotto.

124
00:07:01,850 --> 00:07:04,850
If Dad hadn't stripped all the meat off the bone, you could've had chicken.

125
00:07:06,150 --> 00:07:06,910
Just eat.

126
00:07:06,910 --> 00:07:09,010
Risotto is a good and economical meal.

127
00:07:09,250 --> 00:07:10,990
And it'll last until tomorrow.

128
00:07:11,250 --> 00:07:13,150
We have to cut back because of you anyway.

129
00:07:13,550 --> 00:07:14,750
So you're buying me one?

130
00:07:14,750 --> 00:07:15,230
Eat more.

131
00:07:15,550 --> 00:07:16,530
What are you buying him?

132
00:07:16,590 --> 00:07:17,030
Van Gouda.

133
00:07:17,350 --> 00:07:17,830
Dad.

134
00:07:17,990 --> 00:07:18,430
No.

135
00:07:19,150 --> 00:07:20,620
But you promised!

136
00:07:20,650 --> 00:07:24,540
I said we'll buy a water heater because the co-op won't pay for one thanks to you.

137
00:07:24,750 --> 00:07:26,950
And this taking-turns showering is awful.

138
00:07:27,220 --> 00:07:28,200
They rejected the request?

139
00:07:28,200 --> 00:07:30,320
No, but I found it crumpled up by the dumpsters.

140
00:07:30,320 --> 00:07:31,640
That looks rejected.

141
00:07:33,050 --> 00:07:35,360
I'm not going to eat scraps for something I don't even use.

142
00:07:35,360 --> 00:07:37,980
Oh please, yesterday you used up all the hot water.

143
00:07:38,080 --> 00:07:38,300
Me?

144
00:07:38,480 --> 00:07:39,200
Excuse me!

145
00:07:39,520 --> 00:07:41,180
You went into the bathroom, the shower was running.

146
00:07:41,320 --> 00:07:42,220
I was making the sound with my mouth!

147
00:07:43,160 --> 00:07:46,620
And you still managed to sing Cossack songs at the same time.

148
00:07:46,840 --> 00:07:48,300
Look, I won't stand for this kind of insult.

149
00:07:49,150 --> 00:07:53,450
First they reject my camel and then they accuse me of bathing.

150
00:07:54,010 --> 00:08:04,300
You can't just walk around in a mess.

151
00:08:04,580 --> 00:08:05,380
It's closer from here.

152
00:08:05,520 --> 00:08:06,940
Look, I've got hot water now.

153
00:08:07,180 --> 00:08:08,360
Do they have beer on tap here?

154
00:08:10,050 --> 00:08:11,350
You're in a great mood.

155
00:08:12,100 --> 00:08:13,000
I've had enough.

156
00:08:13,450 --> 00:08:15,050
Nobody listens to me.

157
00:08:15,750 --> 00:08:17,930
We're deciding between buying drums or a shoe rack.

158
00:08:17,930 --> 00:08:18,950
The shoe rack wins.

159
00:08:18,950 --> 00:08:21,450
The diapers finally go on sale and what wins?

160
00:08:21,730 --> 00:08:22,210
A rug.

161
00:08:23,150 --> 00:08:24,550
And they vetoed my camel too.

162
00:08:24,750 --> 00:08:26,350
What would you do with a camel?

163
00:08:27,050 --> 00:08:28,030
It's incredibly versatile.

164
00:08:28,350 --> 00:08:29,350
And beautiful.

165
00:08:29,540 --> 00:08:31,380
We're talking about this two-humped horse.

166
00:08:31,520 --> 00:08:33,340
Yeah, also the one-humped kind, that's called a dromedary.

167
00:08:34,650 --> 00:08:35,850
What would you do with it?

168
00:08:36,420 --> 00:08:38,320
It'd wait for me outside the pub and take me home.

169
00:08:38,420 --> 00:08:41,500
And if the building manager ambushed me at night, it'd spit right in her face.

170
00:08:42,350 --> 00:08:43,590
It really is versatile.

171
00:08:43,710 --> 00:08:44,650
Definitely more than a water heater.

172
00:08:46,610 --> 00:08:47,270
What water heater?

173
00:08:48,120 --> 00:08:49,720
The one they're buying instead of the spitter.

174
00:08:50,020 --> 00:08:50,840
Why a water heater?

175
00:08:51,350 --> 00:08:52,740
Yours is perfectly fine.

176
00:08:52,950 --> 00:08:55,060
Herko, what's everyone's problem, it's not like I bathe.

177
00:08:55,060 --> 00:08:55,720
No, you don't.

178
00:08:56,250 --> 00:08:57,550
You're a tough guy after all.

179
00:08:57,760 --> 00:08:58,420
Exactly.

180
00:08:59,450 --> 00:09:02,050
I just wonder if you've heard anything, maybe second-hand.

181
00:09:03,750 --> 00:09:05,250
Apparently it gives very little hot water.

182
00:09:05,750 --> 00:09:12,250
When a buddy of mine was filling the tub at our place, there was so little hot water his toy boats were scraping the bottom.

183
00:09:13,150 --> 00:09:14,350
My buddy is a sailor.

184
00:09:15,040 --> 00:09:15,520
Sure.

185
00:09:16,450 --> 00:09:17,450
Is my brother home?

186
00:09:17,550 --> 00:09:18,950
I don't care.

187
00:09:22,650 --> 00:09:23,570
I'll be right back.

188
00:09:28,760 --> 00:09:29,240
Hey.

189
00:09:30,610 --> 00:09:31,090
Hi there.

190
00:09:31,090 --> 00:09:32,790
Nothing, just passing by.

191
00:09:32,790 --> 00:09:34,220
You're passing by?

192
00:09:34,220 --> 00:09:35,650
In your underwear?

193
00:09:36,150 --> 00:09:37,750
I just felt like having a coffee.

194
00:09:38,720 --> 00:09:39,540
Want a coffee?

195
00:09:39,720 --> 00:09:39,880
No.

196
00:09:41,050 --> 00:09:42,450
I hear you're buying a water heater.

197
00:09:42,520 --> 00:09:43,420
Yeah, I have to.

198
00:09:43,440 --> 00:09:44,560
Ours is on its last legs.

199
00:09:44,760 --> 00:09:45,560
What kind are you getting?

200
00:09:46,350 --> 00:09:47,960
Well, I was thinking this one.

201
00:09:47,960 --> 00:09:48,380
Small.

202
00:09:50,850 --> 00:09:51,670
How small?

203
00:09:51,670 --> 00:09:54,530
It says right here it's optimal for a family of three.

204
00:09:54,650 --> 00:09:56,350
You'd need one twice as big.

205
00:09:57,930 --> 00:09:58,510
Why?

206
00:09:59,450 --> 00:10:00,250
Just to be safe.

207
00:10:00,550 --> 00:10:02,950
What if someone came to visit.

208
00:10:03,450 --> 00:10:04,750
But nobody ever visits us.

209
00:10:05,760 --> 00:10:06,700
Still.

210
00:10:06,800 --> 00:10:08,460
They lie terribly in those brochures.

211
00:10:08,880 --> 00:10:11,560
They deliberately tell you to buy a smaller one than you need.

212
00:10:13,350 --> 00:10:14,750
And why would they do that?

213
00:10:15,150 --> 00:10:16,130
The smaller one is cheaper.

214
00:10:16,450 --> 00:10:17,250
Exactly.

215
00:10:19,150 --> 00:10:23,570
So wouldn't I expect them to want me to buy the bigger one, since it costs more?

216
00:10:23,750 --> 00:10:25,250
See how you fell for it?

217
00:10:25,550 --> 00:10:29,230
You buy the small one, it's not enough, and then you buy the big one.

218
00:10:29,230 --> 00:10:29,510
Right.

219
00:10:29,570 --> 00:10:30,070
Get it?

220
00:10:30,750 --> 00:10:31,550
They sell two.

221
00:10:37,700 --> 00:10:38,180
Those crooks.

222
00:10:38,730 --> 00:10:40,370
I'm glad you understand.

223
00:10:40,430 --> 00:10:41,150
So the big one.

224
00:10:42,750 --> 00:10:43,750
Who's going to install it?

225
00:10:43,850 --> 00:10:45,440
I don't know, probably some company.

226
00:10:45,440 --> 00:10:45,960
Why not Horvy?

227
00:10:46,940 --> 00:10:47,800
I don't know.

228
00:10:47,920 --> 00:10:49,420
He knows water heaters like nobody else.

229
00:10:49,670 --> 00:10:53,090
I doubt it, it started acting up ever since you brought him in to tune it up.

230
00:10:53,230 --> 00:10:55,450
He clearly said that water heater was on its last legs.

231
00:10:55,510 --> 00:10:57,430
And he tore up the whole bathroom because of it.

232
00:10:57,530 --> 00:11:00,830
I bet without his special condensation pipe you wouldn't even be able to shave.

233
00:11:01,190 --> 00:11:03,330
Well, I'll probably look for someone else.

234
00:11:03,410 --> 00:11:04,810
I'll tell Horvy to give you a good price.

235
00:11:04,850 --> 00:11:05,530
I'm off then!

236
00:11:06,730 --> 00:11:08,230
Wait, you said you'd have a coffee.

237
00:11:08,470 --> 00:11:09,290
It doesn't take me long.

238
00:11:12,750 --> 00:11:32,750
I saw you in the shop window, Mambo, the whole time.

239
00:11:33,270 --> 00:11:33,630
Yeah.

240
00:11:34,550 --> 00:11:40,150
I have an important performance coming up, so I devote every free moment to training.

241
00:11:41,350 --> 00:11:42,350
What did you say?

242
00:11:42,950 --> 00:11:45,250
You couldn't handle proper music.

243
00:12:09,950 --> 00:12:11,950
You'll only break your hat, poor fellow.

244
00:12:12,350 --> 00:12:14,090
Anyone can wiggle their belly.

245
00:12:14,450 --> 00:12:16,070
I'd advise you not to try it.

246
00:12:16,070 --> 00:12:16,530
Why?

247
00:12:17,350 --> 00:12:22,550
You've got so much alcohol in your blood, God knows what would happen if you shook that belly of yours.

248
00:12:31,890 --> 00:12:33,190
I feel great.

249
00:12:43,890 --> 00:12:44,450
Ozzak.

250
00:12:45,990 --> 00:12:46,790
Got a tenner?

251
00:12:47,550 --> 00:12:49,330
Does this look like a kindergarten to you?

252
00:12:49,330 --> 00:12:49,670
Come on!

253
00:12:51,750 --> 00:12:53,190
Hey, how much could a camel cost?

254
00:12:53,450 --> 00:12:54,450
No idea.

255
00:12:54,790 --> 00:12:58,010
Horvat said the butcher pays him a liter per hundred kilos for a pig.

256
00:12:58,470 --> 00:13:00,250
So for a camel it might be similar.

257
00:13:03,150 --> 00:13:04,050
One tenner.

258
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:04,940
That's not enough.

259
00:13:06,110 --> 00:13:06,590
Hang on.

260
00:13:16,210 --> 00:13:16,830
It works!

261
00:13:18,150 --> 00:13:21,510
You slipped me a ten and you'll keep charging my brother twelve.

262
00:13:21,850 --> 00:13:24,510
You want me to cheat my own friend?

263
00:13:24,650 --> 00:13:25,450
We'll split it.

264
00:13:25,760 --> 00:13:26,340
Deal.

265
00:13:33,250 --> 00:13:34,050
Yes, right.

266
00:13:34,250 --> 00:13:38,950
I wanted to ask if a condensation pipe can be mounted on this model.

267
00:13:40,150 --> 00:13:41,450
A condensation pipe.

268
00:13:42,750 --> 00:13:45,250
Well, you should know better what it is, right?

269
00:13:45,740 --> 00:13:46,220
One moment.

270
00:13:47,050 --> 00:13:49,150
Ivuska, go get the door, I'm on the phone.

271
00:13:49,950 --> 00:13:51,750
Okay, I'm back.

272
00:13:51,920 --> 00:13:52,400
One moment.

273
00:13:53,950 --> 00:13:55,710
Go open the door, what if someone's there?

274
00:13:55,850 --> 00:13:57,150
There will be, Marcela is bringing costumes.

275
00:13:58,130 --> 00:13:59,310
What if someone else is there?

276
00:13:59,550 --> 00:14:00,030
So what?

277
00:14:01,050 --> 00:14:01,930
One more moment.

278
00:14:01,930 --> 00:14:02,950
They'll see you.

279
00:14:05,050 --> 00:14:06,550
Okay, I'm back.

280
00:14:06,680 --> 00:14:07,680
So, shall we agree?

281
00:14:07,680 --> 00:14:08,220
For tomorrow?

282
00:14:08,220 --> 00:14:08,620
At five?

283
00:14:09,120 --> 00:14:10,340
Good, I'm looking forward to it.

284
00:14:10,380 --> 00:14:11,640
Alright, just for today.

285
00:14:11,820 --> 00:14:12,500
Who's here?

286
00:14:13,550 --> 00:14:14,450
Nobody else.

287
00:14:32,040 --> 00:14:32,560
Lexa!

288
00:14:33,550 --> 00:14:34,750
Stop spying on Iva!

289
00:14:37,050 --> 00:14:38,250
Good day, Marcelka.

290
00:14:39,850 --> 00:14:41,850
A dignified afternoon, Tomas.

291
00:14:42,350 --> 00:14:44,820
I think I've already apologized, haven't I?

292
00:14:45,050 --> 00:14:47,050
"I meant well" is not an apology.

293
00:14:47,640 --> 00:14:48,160
Ivuska!

294
00:14:49,050 --> 00:14:50,140
I'm coming from the rental shop.

295
00:14:50,140 --> 00:14:51,100
Oh, thank you.

296
00:14:51,880 --> 00:14:52,400
One moment.

297
00:14:53,850 --> 00:14:54,900
That's the whole costume?

298
00:14:55,350 --> 00:14:56,140
Those are two.

299
00:14:56,140 --> 00:14:57,120
For Iva and for Sasa.

300
00:15:00,550 --> 00:15:02,450
This thing can't cover anything at all.

301
00:15:02,650 --> 00:15:04,610
God, it's like a two-piece swimsuit.

302
00:15:04,610 --> 00:15:06,730
You have a two-piece swimsuit?

303
00:15:06,890 --> 00:15:09,510
Dad, please, can you stop embarrassing me in front of strangers?

304
00:15:09,550 --> 00:15:09,830
Thank you.

305
00:15:10,750 --> 00:15:12,550
So I'm embarrassing you?

306
00:15:12,850 --> 00:15:20,210
And aren't you embarrassing yourself, little girl, wanting to writhe around in this nothing in front of some Arab guys?

307
00:15:20,210 --> 00:15:21,430
Tomas, now you're going too far.

308
00:15:21,570 --> 00:15:23,350
The Qatari prince is no brute.

309
00:15:24,540 --> 00:15:25,320
A Qatari prince?

310
00:15:25,380 --> 00:15:26,800
Yes, he confirmed attendance yesterday.

311
00:15:26,860 --> 00:15:28,620
It will be the social event of the year.

312
00:15:29,060 --> 00:15:29,500
Oh God.

313
00:15:29,500 --> 00:15:31,250
You should be proud of Iva.

314
00:15:31,750 --> 00:15:32,340
Proud?

315
00:15:32,340 --> 00:15:35,520
When someone sees her in this, they'll drag her straight to a harem.

316
00:15:35,680 --> 00:15:37,680
Tomas, this is a standard costume.

317
00:15:37,900 --> 00:15:41,420
Last time it was rented by Livie Klausova and nobody dragged her anywhere.

318
00:15:42,240 --> 00:15:43,840
Ivuska will look very lovely in it.

319
00:15:44,450 --> 00:15:46,150
Fine, then let her show me in it.

320
00:15:47,970 --> 00:15:48,730
What's the matter?

321
00:15:49,350 --> 00:15:53,050
If some prince gets to see it, why can't her own father?

322
00:15:54,860 --> 00:15:55,300
Go on.

323
00:16:03,750 --> 00:16:05,070
Tomas, calm down.

324
00:16:05,150 --> 00:16:07,290
The Qatari prince is no slave driver.

325
00:16:07,290 --> 00:16:10,950
Zoran says you won't find a kinder person among arms dealers.

326
00:16:11,790 --> 00:16:14,670
Marcelka, the Orient is a completely different world.

327
00:16:14,690 --> 00:16:16,350
But it's changing, modernizing.

328
00:16:16,750 --> 00:16:20,330
The prince's third wife, for example, has a driver's license completely legally.

329
00:16:20,330 --> 00:16:22,290
The prince arranged an exemption from the law.

330
00:16:30,450 --> 00:16:33,450
Well, I did try to imagine it, but it was even worse.

331
00:16:47,440 --> 00:16:48,000
Hey.

332
00:16:48,680 --> 00:16:49,880
You've got Milos?

333
00:16:50,120 --> 00:16:50,420
Yep.

334
00:16:50,960 --> 00:16:51,440
Wow.

335
00:16:51,440 --> 00:16:56,150
Some kids pulled him out of the basement, thought he was sick, and took him to the vet next door.

336
00:16:56,250 --> 00:16:57,250
Poor things.

337
00:16:58,300 --> 00:16:59,000
Oh well.

338
00:16:59,450 --> 00:17:01,650
A few shots in the belly never killed anyone.

339
00:17:02,120 --> 00:17:02,600
Wow.

340
00:17:03,250 --> 00:17:05,250
Just like the old days.

341
00:17:05,300 --> 00:17:07,180
You, me, and Milos.

342
00:17:07,720 --> 00:17:08,620
Come, let's sit.

343
00:17:10,150 --> 00:17:10,650
Horvy really has it?

344
00:17:11,650 --> 00:17:12,230
Yeah.

345
00:17:12,850 --> 00:17:14,550
You can always count on Horvy.

346
00:17:15,050 --> 00:17:15,750
When's he coming?

347
00:17:15,830 --> 00:17:16,690
Hard to say.

348
00:17:16,690 --> 00:17:19,950
He called saying they threw him off the tram, so now he's riding it.

349
00:17:20,250 --> 00:17:21,250
That's unbelievable.

350
00:17:21,450 --> 00:17:22,730
I'm going to have a spitter.

351
00:17:23,050 --> 00:17:25,750
Well, if you hold out another month on the tenner.

352
00:17:26,750 --> 00:17:27,850
No problem.

353
00:17:39,810 --> 00:17:40,370
Hey.

354
00:17:41,150 --> 00:17:43,350
What are you doing?

355
00:17:44,070 --> 00:17:45,710
Nothing, just stretching.

356
00:17:46,370 --> 00:17:47,230
Want something?

357
00:17:47,670 --> 00:17:48,630
Do you have coffee?

358
00:17:48,750 --> 00:17:49,110
Sure.

359
00:17:52,640 --> 00:17:58,990
Doesn't it make you nervous though?

360
00:17:59,110 --> 00:17:59,410
About what?

361
00:17:59,730 --> 00:18:02,230
That Sasa will be writhing in front of some Arab sheikh.

362
00:18:02,450 --> 00:18:03,130
Totally.

363
00:18:03,510 --> 00:18:05,050
What if he's got his eye on her.

364
00:18:05,910 --> 00:18:06,710
Well yeah.

365
00:18:07,250 --> 00:18:10,830
That prince, a chance like that might not come along again.

366
00:18:10,850 --> 00:18:14,450
It says here he's 60 and has 22 wives.

367
00:18:14,650 --> 00:18:16,030
See, that sounds perfect.

368
00:18:16,350 --> 00:18:19,390
The women are taken care of, they chat, and the men bother them once every two years.

369
00:18:19,390 --> 00:18:20,930
Well, it's against our culture.

370
00:18:21,650 --> 00:18:22,150
Does it say how much he makes?

371
00:18:23,510 --> 00:18:25,090
Yeah, but it's in camels.

372
00:18:25,110 --> 00:18:25,710
Wait, here.

373
00:18:26,950 --> 00:18:31,300
Average monthly income, 7,000 dromedaries.

374
00:18:31,300 --> 00:18:31,740
7,000?

375
00:18:34,350 --> 00:18:35,440
I don't care about that.

376
00:18:35,440 --> 00:18:35,960
Why not?

377
00:18:36,750 --> 00:18:38,850
I've realized a water heater is much better.

378
00:18:39,650 --> 00:18:40,450
Even though I don't bathe.

379
00:18:45,350 --> 00:18:46,050
Pacovsky?

380
00:18:47,250 --> 00:18:49,240
Yeah, you're the water heater guy.

381
00:18:49,240 --> 00:18:50,440
Who's the water heater guy?

382
00:18:50,480 --> 00:18:50,960
One moment.

383
00:18:52,150 --> 00:18:54,000
I ended up hiring a different company.

384
00:18:54,250 --> 00:18:55,550
Well, I'm already here.

385
00:18:56,230 --> 00:18:57,650
Yeah, you're waiting in front of the building.

386
00:18:58,050 --> 00:18:58,950
That soon, huh?

387
00:18:59,740 --> 00:19:00,880
Well, I'd better get down there.

388
00:19:01,700 --> 00:19:02,760
Thanks, great coffee.

389
00:19:03,020 --> 00:19:04,180
It's the water.

390
00:19:08,550 --> 00:19:11,450
Lexa, listen to me carefully now.

391
00:19:17,680 --> 00:19:19,960
Come on, don't tell me we haven't met before.

392
00:19:20,350 --> 00:19:22,630
You remind me so much of someone.

393
00:19:23,950 --> 00:19:26,850
I'd be very surprised.

394
00:19:27,550 --> 00:19:33,250
This is my first time in this building, ausgerechnet, as we plumbers say.

395
00:19:37,950 --> 00:19:38,350
But what?

396
00:19:41,360 --> 00:19:41,840
Damn.

397
00:19:57,650 --> 00:19:58,350
What an idiot.

398
00:20:09,250 --> 00:20:09,750
And sorry again for locking you in the cellar.

399
00:20:12,460 --> 00:20:13,140
Yeah, no problem.

400
00:20:13,340 --> 00:20:15,260
And is your bathroom worth the hassle now?

401
00:20:16,750 --> 00:20:17,860
The condensation pipe.

402
00:20:18,250 --> 00:20:18,850
That's a good one.

403
00:20:19,150 --> 00:20:20,450
You really fell for it, huh?

404
00:20:21,450 --> 00:20:22,450
Yeah, what an artist.

405
00:20:22,630 --> 00:20:24,010
What was your name again?

406
00:20:24,450 --> 00:20:24,850
Pacovsky.

407
00:20:24,930 --> 00:20:26,830
Right, Pacovsky, sure, sure.

408
00:20:26,910 --> 00:20:29,370
I don't wanna get it wrong when I tell the guys at the shop.

409
00:20:29,470 --> 00:20:30,590
Because they won't believe me anyway.

410
00:20:30,730 --> 00:20:31,930
I guarantee it. Goodbye.

411
00:20:33,550 --> 00:20:34,350
Goodbye.

412
00:20:37,960 --> 00:20:38,360
Dad.

413
00:20:38,540 --> 00:20:38,860
No.

414
00:20:40,750 --> 00:20:42,630
Do you realize how long we've been training?

415
00:20:42,750 --> 00:20:43,950
You'll thank me one day.

416
00:20:44,150 --> 00:20:46,550
Arab women will keep walking around in sacks because of you.

417
00:20:46,850 --> 00:20:47,550
You too.

418
00:20:47,650 --> 00:20:52,680
Dad, Sasa won't go without me and Marcelka can't dance a herd of mares by herself.

419
00:20:52,680 --> 00:20:53,820
She'll manage.

420
00:21:01,750 --> 00:21:04,650
Marcelka, Iva, could you please talk to my father?

421
00:21:04,850 --> 00:21:07,350
Yeah, he won't let me go to the performance.

422
00:21:08,450 --> 00:21:09,350
What do you mean, in the cellar?

423
00:21:10,250 --> 00:21:11,350
Who locked you in?

424
00:21:12,150 --> 00:21:12,950
Your husband?

425
00:21:14,650 --> 00:21:17,450
Ah, he saw you rehearsing in the costume.

426
00:21:18,450 --> 00:21:18,950
Exactly.

427
00:21:36,950 --> 00:21:39,460
Ivuska, thank God, you're not in the cellar.

428
00:21:39,460 --> 00:21:42,340
That husband of Marcelka's must have Arab ancestors.

429
00:21:42,460 --> 00:21:44,020
He treats her like a slave.

430
00:21:44,140 --> 00:21:44,860
He's not the only one.

431
00:21:45,270 --> 00:21:45,630
What?

432
00:21:45,630 --> 00:21:49,450
The grand vizier here put me under house arrest too.

433
00:21:49,810 --> 00:21:50,770
Pacovsky, hello.

434
00:21:50,970 --> 00:21:51,630
It won't work without her.

435
00:21:52,450 --> 00:21:54,170
I can't dance a herd of mares alone.

436
00:21:54,170 --> 00:21:54,450
See?

437
00:21:55,050 --> 00:21:57,770
My daughter is no mare.

438
00:21:57,950 --> 00:22:00,150
Mr. Pacovsky, you don't understand.

439
00:22:00,350 --> 00:22:03,250
Performing for the Qatari prince is an enormous honor.

440
00:22:03,450 --> 00:22:06,950
If this goes well, it opens the door to all the Arab capitals.

441
00:22:07,450 --> 00:22:09,750
I've been waiting my whole life for an opportunity like this.

442
00:22:10,750 --> 00:22:11,850
Not a chance.

443
00:22:13,750 --> 00:22:15,050
Goodbye, Cairo.

444
00:22:16,550 --> 00:22:18,110
Maybe you and Sasa could manage.

445
00:22:18,450 --> 00:22:19,090
Who's Sasa?

446
00:22:19,250 --> 00:22:20,450
The one with the chestnut in her belly button.

447
00:22:21,450 --> 00:22:22,850
Goodbye, Cairo.

448
00:22:25,900 --> 00:22:26,500
Hey.

449
00:22:27,080 --> 00:22:27,680
Hi.

450
00:22:27,720 --> 00:22:28,160
Hey.

451
00:22:28,950 --> 00:22:32,050
I'm so sorry we have to part ways like this.

452
00:22:32,350 --> 00:22:33,000
A tenner.

453
00:22:33,450 --> 00:22:34,960
But it's my final offer.

454
00:22:34,960 --> 00:22:42,910
Who is that?

455
00:22:43,230 --> 00:22:44,010
My brother.

456
00:22:44,010 --> 00:22:48,960
Where did he learn the Bengali style?

457
00:22:48,960 --> 00:22:49,820
What, Ozzak?

458
00:22:49,820 --> 00:22:51,750
Look, he's doing figure eights.

459
00:22:55,150 --> 00:22:56,650
That shoulder accent.

460
00:22:57,950 --> 00:23:01,140
Excuse me, did you study under Fatima?

461
00:23:01,750 --> 00:23:02,850
No, under Simona.

462
00:23:03,350 --> 00:23:05,350
That must be an excellent school.

463
00:23:06,150 --> 00:23:07,950
Would you have two hours free?

464
00:23:08,450 --> 00:23:10,950
You could even meet the Qatari prince.

465
00:23:11,450 --> 00:23:12,780
That's the one with the camels.

466
00:23:12,780 --> 00:23:15,920
And he can be incredibly generous.

467
00:23:15,920 --> 00:23:21,130
He put his three favorite dromedaries up in the presidential suite at the Hilton.

468
00:23:21,350 --> 00:23:22,550
Ozzak is a real man.

469
00:23:23,150 --> 00:23:24,650
He's got a great figure.

470
00:23:24,950 --> 00:23:25,420
Thanks.

471
00:23:25,750 --> 00:23:28,450
And once he's in the costume, nobody will notice.

472
00:23:28,750 --> 00:23:30,320
What about the mustache?

473
00:23:30,550 --> 00:23:32,750
Have you ever seen the prince's third wife?

474
00:23:38,150 --> 00:23:44,570
According to the driver of tram number 15, the trail of the llama stolen from the Prague Zoo ends at the Letenske namesti stop.

475
00:23:44,570 --> 00:23:49,850
I originally thought it was just some big dog, but it didn't have a muzzle, so I let it off here.

476
00:23:51,430 --> 00:23:52,010
Nowhere.

477
00:23:52,850 --> 00:23:54,150
I'll open it myself.

478
00:24:04,250 --> 00:24:08,040
Simona, you really went too far with that condensation pipe.

479
00:24:08,250 --> 00:24:11,000
Stop being angry, we need to wash ourselves sometimes too.

480
00:24:11,000 --> 00:24:11,720
Come on.

481
00:24:14,880 --> 00:24:15,460
Schnitzel?

482
00:24:16,350 --> 00:24:18,150
Sasa just finished frying them.

483
00:24:19,060 --> 00:24:20,760
Look, I'm using a bit of hot water.

484
00:24:20,820 --> 00:24:21,520
It's the principle.

485
00:24:21,820 --> 00:24:23,620
Great, so you don't mind if I take a shower?

486
00:24:23,700 --> 00:24:25,400
Horvat and I worked really hard.

487
00:24:25,600 --> 00:24:27,260
And he can stay out of my sight too.

488
00:24:27,340 --> 00:24:30,060
Now all the plumbers in the neighborhood are laughing at me because of him.

489
00:24:30,240 --> 00:24:32,600
Well, Horvy was always a real joker.

490
00:24:34,350 --> 00:24:35,450
Is it good?

491
00:24:35,850 --> 00:24:37,020
Exotic meat.

492
00:24:37,020 --> 00:24:38,540
I've still got 50 kilos of it.

493
00:24:38,940 --> 00:24:39,660
So can I?

494
00:24:41,000 --> 00:24:41,640
Fine.

495
00:24:46,950 --> 00:24:49,990
Alright, go ahead, and don't use up all the water or I'll deal with you.

496
00:24:49,990 --> 00:24:50,470
Go!

497
00:24:51,070 --> 00:24:51,870
Water fight!

498
00:24:58,350 --> 00:25:00,750
Yes, Mrs. Building Manager, you can count on me.

499
00:25:01,250 --> 00:25:04,050
Yes, there won't be any more problems with my brother.

500
00:25:04,550 --> 00:25:06,850
Right, yes, I'll keep an eye on him.

501
00:25:07,550 --> 00:25:09,200
No, bear with me, but from next week it's over.

502
00:25:09,200 --> 00:25:10,400
I understand, certainly.

503
00:25:12,150 --> 00:25:13,650
Well, then it couldn't have been him.

504
00:25:15,050 --> 00:25:16,850
Oh, then it probably was him.

505
00:25:17,150 --> 00:25:21,750
No, no, of course I don't want to lose access to the common areas, or the cellar.

506
00:25:21,850 --> 00:25:27,540
Yes, right, no, Mrs. Building Manager, you're kind, I know you let us off conditionally, I appreciate it.

507
00:25:27,550 --> 00:25:30,040
Mrs. Building Manager, I'll set my brother straight.

508
00:25:30,040 --> 00:25:31,780
He'll behave like clockwork.

509
00:25:31,920 --> 00:25:33,940
I've had a very good influence on him lately.

510
00:25:34,080 --> 00:25:35,100
Yes, a very good influence.

511
00:25:36,250 --> 00:25:39,210
Yes, yes, of course no stomping on the stairs.

512
00:25:39,450 --> 00:25:40,890
Yes, no yelling.

513
00:25:40,890 --> 00:25:42,890
Yes, absolutely no spitting.

514
00:25:42,950 --> 00:25:45,350
No spitting, that I can swear to.

515
00:25:46,650 --> 00:25:50,850
Yes, Mrs. Building Manager, thank you, goodbye, and I think everything will be just fine.
